            <field>
              <name>HT</name>
              <description>Hold Time. The formatting scheme can become inefficient when fast switching occurs, and you can use this setting to minimize switching. 
          When a source has nothing to transmit, then another source is selected irrespective of the minimum number of transactions. 
          The ATB funnel holds for the minimum hold time and one additional transaction. The actual hold time is the register value plus 1. 
          The maximum value that can be entered is 0b1110 and this equates to 15 transactions. 0b1111 is reserved.</description>
              <lsb>8</lsb>
              <msb>11</msb>
            </field>
