        <register>
          <name>RETAIN</name>
          <description>RETAIN of each individual GPIO pin. Pins with their RETAIN bit set keep their state independent of changes of the
        GPIO-configuration and peripheral changes. RETAIN must be cleared before the pin can be used. RETAIN is
        typically used to isolate the pin state from internal device state changes. The pin will keep
        all its state including the output value, DIR and PORTCNF settings.</description>
          <addressOffset>0x040</addressOffset>
          <access>read-write</access>
          <resetValue>0xFFFFFFFF</resetValue>
          <size>0x20</size>
